name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 12/ Remember that this will DEFINITELY PASS and the last thing you want to is come out of this thinking you could have bought more!

name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 11/ MAKE SURE YOU BUY ENOUGH. Bear markets like this are a gift & a rare opportunity. We now know that blockchain isn't going anywhere, except mainstream & when it is financial markets that are killing us we must accept the rare gift we are given!

name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 10/ Look at fully diluted valuations only. Chances are that any other valuation is a scam and that you will be diluted more and more as the bear market get longer! You will literally drown in token releases the longer the bear market goes on for.

name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 9/ Use this time to build a well diversified portfolio across narratives and chains. Don't over-invest in any single chain or narrative. $LUNA taught us that anything can fail no matter how much we believe in it!

name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 8/ Use this time to learn as much as you can, without the hype and with the FOMO. You have time now to go in depth without missing any urgent trades. Build your skills in research, staking, trading etc..

name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 7/ Block out the noise! Clean up your twitter/youtube feeds and other subscriptions. By now you probably know who is value and who is just noise. Keeps the ones that have been here before and be vigilant in your clean-up!

name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 6/ Don't get wiped out by a silly mistake! Get your tokens of exchanges and protect your keys! It would be a shame if you survived the whole bear and lost what you accumulate to a rookie mistake!

name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 5/ Get out of any project that isn't well funded, isn't shipping or isn't being used! DO IT TODAY! Forget about what the prices were in the bull. They were unrealistic & won't be seen again! The market has no memory doesn't care that your favourite shitcoin is 90% from its high!

name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 3/Spend less time on twitter. Twitter is an echo chamber for mainstream sentiment. In a bear market you should use it only to gauge when sentiment is low enough to start buying.

name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 2/Stop looking at the screen. Checking prices in a bull market is fun, it re-affirms what a genius you actually are 🤣! In a bear market it will not only distract you from the fundamentals but sudden temporary price declines may also cause you to panic and sell.

name: Ran Neuner
tweet: 1/Firstly, come to terms with the fact that the bear market will last way longer than you anticipated, just like the bull market ended way sooner than you predicted. A bull market is a sprint, a bear market is a marathon. Prepare yourself mentally for a tough road ahead!
